Enforce cross-platform filename hygiene for file create/rename operations

Description:
  - Filenames must consist exclusively of ASCII letters (A–Z, a–z), digits (0–9), hyphens (-), underscores (_), and a single period (.) separating the basename and extension.
  - Prohibited: null character, directory separators (/ on POSIX, \ on Windows), Windows-forbidden symbols (< > : " / \ | ? *), whitespace (spaces, tabs, newlines), and names starting or ending with hyphens, underscores, periods, or whitespace.
  - Length constraints: filename (basename + extension) ≤ 255 characters; total path length < 260 characters.

Validation Regex:
  ^(?!.{256,})(?!(?i:CON|PRN|AUX|NUL|COM[1-9]|LPT[1-9])(?:\.|$))[A-Za-z0-9](mdc:?:[A-Za-z0-9_-]{0,253}[A-Za-z0-9])?(?:\.[A-Za-z0-9_-]+)?$
